# Sasko's Kitchen ï¿½ part2
Features of the CSS

1. General Reset
CSS
  margin: 0.
  padding: 0.
  box-sizing: border-box.
Resets default browser spacing
Ensure consistent box-sizing across all elements.

2. Body Styling 
  font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif.
  line-height: 1.6.
  background-color: white
  color: black
Applied a clean font for readability.
Light background (white) with dark text for contrast.
Line height improves text spacing.

3. Header & Navigation
header
  background: dark blue.
  color: white.
  padding: 1.5rem.
  text-align center.

Dark blue background with white text.
Center-aligned header content.
Navigation menu uses flexbox for horizontal layout with spacing.
nav ul li a: hover,
nav ul li a. active 
  color: red
Links highlight red on hover or when active.

4. About Page Sections
section image
  border: 3px solid dark blue.
  box-shadow: 0 3px 8px rgba (0,0,0,0.2).
Added borders and shadow around images for a polished look.

section article
  background: white.
  padding: 1rem.
  border-radius: 10px.
  margin-bottom: 1rem.
  box-shadow: 0 2px 6px rgba (0,0,0,0.1).

Team member descriptions are styled as cards with rounded corners and shadows.

5. Forms (Reusable CSS for Order/Contact Pages)
  background: white.
  padding: 1.5rem.
  border-radius: 10px.
  box-shadow: 0 2px 6px rgba (0,0,0,0.1).
Clean white card-style forms.
Labels bold and spaced.
Inputs styled with padding, border-radius, and spacing.

6. Buttons
button 
  background: dark blue.
  color: white.
  padding: 0.8rem 1.5rem.
  border: none.
  border-radius: 6px.
  font-size: 1rem.
  cursor: pointer.
  transition: background 0.3s.

button: hover 
background: dark red.
Dark blue button with white text.
Smooth hover effect turns background dark red.

7. Footer
  background: dark blue.
  color: white.
text-align center.
padding: 1.5rem 1rem.
margin-top: 2rem.
Matches header styling for consistency.
Links styled bold and highlighted on hover.

8. Responsive Design
media (max-width: 768px)
nav ul 
flex-direction: column.
    gap: 0.5rem.
  main
    padding: 1rem.
  
Navigation becomes vertical on smaller screens.
Extra padding inside main for mobile readability.

